{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":14818025,"datasetId":9476157,"databundleVersionId":15674684}],"dockerImageVersionId":31259,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/himanimalhotra/power-bi-travel-booking-dashboard-project?scriptVersionId=301283970\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Revenue Intelligence & Channel Performance Analysis | Power BI Project","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### By Himani Malhotra","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Business Problem**\n\nBusinesses operating in booking-driven industries such as travel, hospitality, or services rely heavily on optimizing revenue, managing discounts, and minimizing cancellations.\n\nKey challenges addressed in this analysis:\n\n•\tLack of visibility into revenue performance across categories and channels\n\n•\tUncertainty about whether discounts were improving demand or reducing profitability\n\n•\tRevenue leakage due to cancellations and refunds\n\n•\tLimited understanding of geographic performance trends\n\n•\tNeed for centralized KPI tracking for leadership decision-making\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Project Objective**\n\nThe objective of this project was to analyze booking and revenue data to:\n\n•\tTrack overall business performance using key metrics\n\n•\tIdentify top-performing and underperforming categories\n\n•\tEvaluate acquisition channel efficiency\n\n•\tAnalyze the impact of discounts on bookings and revenue\n\n•\tIdentify revenue loss due to cancellations and refunds\n\n•\tProvide actionable insights to improve profitability and operational efficiency\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Business Questions to be answered:\n\n• Which categories generate the highest revenue?\n\n• Which acquisition channels drive the most bookings and revenue?\n\n• Are discounts effectively increasing demand or hurting profitability?\n\n• Which categories or channels have the highest cancellation rates?\n\n• Which cities contribute the most to revenue?\n\n• What factors contribute to revenue loss (refunds, cancellations)?\n\n• Which channels are most efficient vs discount-dependent?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Dashboard \n\n Dashboard Preview and Screenshots added in Comments due to Kaggle limitations\n\n#### [Dashboard in GitHub](https://github.com/himanimalhotra17/Travel-Booking-Dashboard-PowerBi)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Dataset Overview\n\nThe dataset included transactional booking-level data with the following key fields:\n\n•\tBooking ID\n\n•\tBooking Date\n\n•\tCategory\n\n•\tChannel\n\n•\tCity\n\n•\tBooking Status\n\n•\tBase Price\n\n•\tFinal Price\n\n•\tDiscount Percentage\n\n•\tNet Revenue\n\n•\tRefund Amount\n\nThe dataset enabled multi-dimensional analysis across time, geography, category, and acquisition channel.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)**\n\nThe following KPIs were developed to track business performance:\n\n•\tTotal Bookings\n\n•\tTotal Net Revenue\n\n•\tAverage Revenue per Booking\n\n•\tCancellation Rate\n\n•\tAverage Discount Percentage\n\n•\tTotal Refund Amount\n\n•\tRevenue by Category\n\n•\tRevenue by Channel\n\n•\tRevenue by City \n\nThese KPIs provided a comprehensive view of business health and operational efficiency.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Tools & Skills Used**\n\n#### Tools & Tech used:\n\n•\tPower BI (Dashboard development and visualization)\n\n•\tDAX (Data Analysis Expressions for KPI creation)\n\n•\tExcel (Data source)\n\n•\tData modeling techniques (Date table, relationships, calculated measures)\n\n\n#### Key Skills Demonstrated:\n\n• Data cleaning and transformation\n\n• Business performance and trend analysis\n\n• KPI development\n\n• Churn and retention proxy analysis\n\n• Revenue optimization and profitability analysis\n\n• Dashboard design and visualization\n\n• Data modeling using Power BI\n\n• Business insight generation","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Dashboard Features\n\nThis Dashboard includes:\n\n• Executive KPI summary\n\n• Revenue and booking trends\n\n• Category and channel performance analysis\n\n• Discount impact analysis\n\n• Cancellation and refund analysis\n\n• Churn and retention analysis\n\n• Geographic performance analysis\n\n• Business Insights and Recommendations\n\n• Interactive filters and drill-down capability","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Step-by-Step Process to create Power BI dashboard","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### **STEP 1: Import Data into Power BI**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Open Power BI Desktop\n\nClick:\n\nHome → Get Data → Excel → Select your file\n\nSelect your sheet → Click Load","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Click: Transform Data\n\nCheck and fix the necessary Column Names.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Ensure correct data types as:\n\n| Column         | Data Type      |\n| -------------- | -------------- |\n| Booking_ID     | Text           |\n| Booking_Date   | Date           |\n| Category       | Text           |\n| Channel        | Text           |\n| City           | Text           |\n| Booking_Status | Text           |\n| Base_Price     | Decimal Number |\n| Final_Price    | Decimal Number |\n| Discount_%     | Decimal Number |\n| Net_Revenue    | Decimal Number |\n| Refund_Amount  | Decimal Number |\n\nClick: Close & Apply","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 3: Create Date Column**\n\nClick: Modeling → New Column\n\nADDCOLUMNS(\n    \"Month\", FORMAT([Booking_Date], \"MMM\"),\n    \"Year-Month\", FORMAT([Booking_Date], \"YYYY-MMM\")\n)\n\nClick: Close & Apply","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 4: Create Core KPI Measures**\n\nClick Modeling → New Measure\n\n\nCreate these:\n\n#### Total Bookings\n\nTotal Bookings = COUNT([Booking_ID])\n\n#### Total Revenue\n\nTotal Revenue = SUM([Net_Revenue])\n\n#### Avg Revenue per Booking\n\nAvg Revenue per Booking = DIVIDE([Total Revenue], [Total Bookings])\n\n#### Cancellation Rate\n\nCancelled Bookings = \nCALCULATE(\n    COUNT([Booking_ID]),\n    [Booking_Status] = \"Cancelled\"\n)\n\nCancellation Rate = \nDIVIDE([Cancelled Bookings], [Total Bookings])\n\nFormat as %\n\n#### Average Discount % \n\nAvg Discount = AVERAGE([Discount_%])\n\n#### Total Refund\n\nTotal Refund = SUM([Refund_Amount])","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 5: Build Executive Summary Page**\n\nRename page: Executive Summary\n\n**1. Add KPI Cards**\n\nInsert → Card\n\nAdd: Total Bookings, Total Revenue, Avg Revenue per Booking, Cancellation Rate, Avg Discount, Total Refund\n\n**2. Add Charts**\n\n***Revenue Trend***\n\nInsert → Line Chart\n\nAxis: Year-Month\n\nValues:Total Revenue\n\nCan also add:\nTotal Bookings\n\n***Revenue by Category***\n\nInsert → Bar Chart\n\nAxis:Category\n\nValues:Total Revenue\n\n***Revenue by Channel***\n\nInsert → Bar Chart\n\nAxis:Channel\n\nValues:Total Revenue","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 6: Build Category Analysis Page**\n\nCreate new page → Rename: Category Analysis\n\nAdd visuals:\n\n***Revenue by Category***\n\nBar chart\n\nAxis: Category\nValue: Total Revenue\n\n***Bookings by Category***\n\nBar chart\n\nAxis: Category\nValue: Total Bookings\n\n***Cancellation Rate by Category***\n\nBar chart\n\nAxis: Category\nValue: Cancellation Rate\n\n***Avg Discount% by Category***\n\nBar chart\n\nAxis: Category\nValue: Avg Discount","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 7: Build Channel Analysis Page**\n\nNew page → Channel Analysis\n\nAdd:\n\n***Revenue by Channel***\n\n***Bookings by Channel***\n\n***Cancellation Rate by Channel***\n\n***Avg Discount% by Channel***\n\n***Refund Amount by Channel***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 8: Build Discount Analysis Page**\n\nNew page → Discount Analysis\n\nAdd Scatter Chart\n\nInsert → Scatter Chart\n\nAdd:\n***Avg Discount % vs Bookings***\n\nX axis → Avg Discount\nY axis → Total Bookings\nLegend → Channel/ Category\nSize → Total Revenue\n\n***Avg Discount % by Channel***\n\n***Avg Discount % by Category***\n\n***Discount Trend***\n\nThis shows:\n\nWhich channels rely on discounts?\n\nDoes discount increase demand?\n\nWhich channels are efficient?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Discount Analysis Insights & Implications:**\n\n1. Hotels offer the highest average discount (~23%) and also have the highest booking volume.\n\n->Hotels are over-discounting → optimize discount strategy to improve margins.\n\n2. Flights achieve strong booking volume with significantly lower discount (~8%), indicating strong organic demand.\n\n->Flights category has strong pricing power → opportunity to reduce discounts further.\n\n3. Packages require moderate discounts (~12%) but generate the lowest booking volume, suggesting weaker demand elasticity.\n\n->Packages need demand stimulation beyond discounts (marketing, bundling, UX improvements).","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 9: Build Cancellation & Refund Analysis Page**\n\nNew page → Cancellation Analysis\n\nAdd:\n\n***Cancellation Rate% by Category***\n\n***Cancellation Rate% by Channel***\n\n***Refund by Category***\n\n***Refund Trend over time***\n\n***Cancellation Trend***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 10: Build City Analysis Page**\n\nInsert → Map Visual\n\nLocation:City\n\nSize:Total Revenue\n\nTooltip:Total Bookings\n\n***Bookings by City***\n\n***Cancellation Rate% by City***\n\n***Revenue by City***\n\n***Avg Discount % by City***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Churn rate: % of customers who stop using the service over a period of timeor Customers active last period but NOT active this period / Customers active last period**\n\nSince Customer Id is not present in the dataset, we cannot measure: Repeat customers-Customer retention-True churn rate\nCustomer_ID & Booking_Date is needed to calculate TRUE churn rate.\n\nLet's understand with an Example:\n\n|Customer|\tJan\t|Feb  |Churn    |\n|--------|------|-----|---------|\n|A       |  Yes |No → |    Churn|\n|B\t     |  Yes |Yes →| Retained|\n\nCalculation if Customer_ID existed:\n\nChurned Customers = CALCULATE( DISTINCTCOUNT([Customer_ID]), EXCEPT( VALUES([Customer_ID] in Previous Month), VALUES([Customer_ID] in Current Month) ) )\n\nSince Customer_ID is unavailable, true churn couldn't be calculated. Instead, we can create churn proxies to identify revenue leakage and retention risks.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 11: Build Retention & Churn Analysis Page** \n\n#### **Operational Churn**: Customers who left before completing a transaction\n\nOperational Churn =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    COUNTROWS(FILTER(Bookings_Data,[Booking_Status]=\"Cancelled\")),\n    COUNTROWS(Bookings_Data)\n)\n\n#### **Revenue Churn**: Shows revenue lost after booking\n\nRevenue Churn =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    SUM([Refund_Amount]),\n    SUM([Net_Revenue])\n)\n\n#### **Channel Drop-off Rate**: Shows which acquisition channels bring low-quality users\n % of bookings from each channel that resulted in cancellation.\n\nChannel Drop-off Rate =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    CALCULATE(\n        COUNT([Booking_ID]),\n        [Booking_Status] = \"Cancelled\"\n    ),\n    CALCULATE(\n        COUNT([Booking_ID]),\n        ALLEXCEPT(Bookings_Data,[Channel])\n    )\n)\n\n\n#### **Category Retention Proxy**: Bookings trend over time per category\n\nIf bookings drop consistently → demand churn/retention problem\n\nStep 1: Monthly bookings measure\nMonthly Bookings =\nCOUNT([Booking_ID])\n\nStep 2: Previous month bookings\nPrevious Month Bookings =\nCALCULATE(\n    [Monthly Bookings],\n    DATEADD([Booking_Date], -1, MONTH)\n)\n\nStep 3: Retention Proxy Rate\nCategory Retention Proxy =\nDIVIDE(\n    [Monthly Bookings],\n    [Previous Month Bookings]\n)\n\n| Value | Meaning       |\n|-------|---------------|\n| 1.0   | stable demand |\n|  >1   | growing       |\n| <1    | demand loss   |\n\n#### **Customer Intent Loss Rate**: Measures lost customers at final stage\n\nIntent Loss Rate = Cancelled Bookings/Total Bookings\n\n% of customers who showed intent (booked) but did not complete transaction.\n\nHigh value = serious churn risk.\n\nUse in dashboard\nVisual:\n• By Channel\n• By Category\n• Trend over time\n\n#### **Revenue Loss Rate** - % revenue lost due to refunds (Shows financial churn)\n\nRevenue Loss Rate =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    SUM([Refund_Amount]),\n    SUM([Net_Revenue])\n)\n\n#### **Discount Dependency Ratio** - Shows how much bookings rely on discounts (High value = artificial demand)\n\nDiscount Dependency =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    AVERAGE([Discount_%]),\n    AVERAGE([Base_Price])\n)\n\n#### **Net Revenue Retention Proxy** - Measures how much revenue survives cancellations/refunds.\n\nNet Revenue Retention =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    SUM([Net_Revenue]) - SUM([Refund_Amount]),\n    SUM([Net_Revenue])\n)\n\n#### **Booking Survival Rate** - Opposite of churn.\n\nBooking Survival Rate =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    CALCULATE(\n        COUNT([Booking_ID]),\n       [Booking_Status] = \"Completed\"\n    ),\n    COUNT(Bookings_Data[Booking_ID])\n)\n#### **Channel Quality Score** - [Higher score = better channel]\n\nChannel Quality Score =\nDIVIDE(\n    SUM([Net_Revenue]),\n    COUNT([Booking_ID])\n)\n\n#### **Refund Probability by Channel** - Shows risky acquisition sources.\n\nRefund Rate =\n\nDIVIDE(\n    COUNT([Refund_Amount]),\n    COUNT([Booking_ID])\n)\n\n#### **Revenue at Risk** - Revenue at Risk = SUM([Refund_Amount])\n\n\n\n**This page will show:**\n\n• Customer churn proxy analysis\n\n• Channel quality analysis\n\n• Revenue retention analysis\n\n• Demand retention analysis\n\n• Revenue risk analysis\n\n#### **Key Insights:**\n\n• Paid Ads channels show higher customer intent loss, indicating low-quality acquisition sources\n\n• Affiliate channel has highest drop-off rate, indicating poor traffic quality.\n\n• Revenue retention analysis highlights measurable revenue leakage due to cancellations and refunds\n\n• Category demand trends reveal differences in customer retention across service segments\n\n• Channel quality score identifies high-efficiency and low-efficiency acquisition channels\n\n• Revenue risk analysis highlights areas requiring operational improvement","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 12: Add Slicers to make dashboard interactive**\n\nInsert slicers for:\n\nBooking_Date(Year, Month)\n\nCategory\n\nChannel\n\nCity\n\nBooking_Status\n\nPlace slicers on left panel.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 13: Add Drill-through Page (Advanced feature)**\n\nCreate new page → Name: Detail View\n\nAdd table with:\n\nBooking_ID\n\nCategory\n\nChannel\n\nCity\n\nRevenue\n\nDiscount\n\nAdd Drill-through filter:\n\nCategory\n\nNow users can right-click category → see detailed data.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 14: Create Insights Page**\n\nCreate page → Insights \n\nAdd text box and write insights like:\n\nKey Insights:\n\n• Flights generate highest revenue but also highest cancellations\n\n• Paid Ads have high bookings but require heavy discounting\n\n• Direct channel generates best revenue efficiency\n\n• Some cities show high revenue potential but low penetration\n\nThis shows business thinking.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 15: Design Like a Professional Dashboard**\n\nUse:\n\n• Consistent colors\n• Light background\n• Proper alignment\n• Section headers\n\nUse:\n\nView → Themes → Choose professional theme","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 16: Final Dashboard Structure**\n\nYour final dashboard should have:\n\nPage 1: Executive Summary\n\nPage 2: Category Analysis\n\nPage 3: Channel Analysis\n\nPage 4: Discount Analysis\n\nPage 5: Cancellation Analysis\n\nPage 6: Geographic Analysis\n\nPage 7: Retention & Churn Analysis\n\nPage 8: Business Insights & Recommendations\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **STEP 17: Export for Portfolio**\n\nFile → Export → PDF\n\nor\n\nPublish → Power BI Service","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Strategy\n### ***Executive thinking → Performance diagnosis → Root cause analysis → Retention & revenue protection.***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### **Technical Implementation**\n\nThe dashboard was built using the following techniques:\n\n•\tData cleaning and transformation using Power BI Power Query\n\n•\tCreation of calculated measures using DAX\n\n•\tDevelopment of a date dimension table for time-based analysis\n\n•\tImplementation of interactive filters and slicers\n\n•\tUse of drill-down and drill-through features for detailed analysis\n\n•\tVisualization of trends, comparisons, and performance metrics\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Key Business Insights and Recommendations**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **1. Revenue is concentrated in a few key categories**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nA small number of categories contribute a disproportionately large share of total revenue, indicating a dependence on specific service segments that creates both opportunity and risk.A small number of categories contributed the majority of total revenue, indicating dependency on key service segments.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nRevenue concentration analysis revealed reliance on a few core categories, highlighting opportunities for diversification and growth optimization. Focus on scaling high-performing categories while improving performance in underperforming ones.\n\n#### **2. Certain channels generate volume but not efficient revenue**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nSome acquisition channels drive high booking volume but show lower average revenue per booking and higher discount dependency.These channels bring lower-quality or price-sensitive customers.Some acquisition channels generated high booking volume but required significantly higher discounts, reducing overall profitability.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nChannel analysis revealed differences in acquisition efficiency, with certain channels requiring higher discounts to drive bookings, reducing overall revenue efficiency. Reallocate marketing spend toward higher-efficiency channels.\n\n#### **3. High discounts do not always lead to proportional booking growth**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nIncreasing discounts did not consistently result in higher booking volumes across all categories and channels.Discounts are sometimes reducing profitability without increasing demand.Higher discounts did not always result in proportional increases in bookings, suggesting inefficient discount allocation.Categories with lower discount dependency demonstrated higher average revenue per booking and better revenue efficiency.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nOptimize discount allocation.Reduce excessive discounting in channels where discounts do not significantly increase bookings.Discount effectiveness analysis showed diminishing returns beyond certain discount levels, indicating opportunities to optimize pricing strategy.\n\n#### **4. Measurable revenue loss due to cancellations and refunds**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nCancellation and refund analysis showed clear revenue leakage across certain channels and categories.This represents lost revenue and operational inefficiency.Cancellation and refund trends revealed measurable revenue loss, highlighting operational inefficiencies and customer drop-off points.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nInvestigate root causes of cancellations.Cancellation analysis identified revenue leakage, highlighting opportunities to improve customer experience and operational processes.Identify root causes of high cancellation categories and implement targeted operational improvements.\n\n#### **5. Channel quality varies significantly**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nSome channels generate higher revenue per booking and lower cancellation rates.These are high-value acquisition channels.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nIncrease investment in high-quality channels.Channel quality scoring identified high-performing acquisition sources with stronger revenue efficiency and lower churn risk.\n\n#### **6. Geographic performance is uneven**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nRevenue is concentrated in specific cities, while other cities show lower penetration.Growth opportunities exist in underpenetrated markets.A few cities contributed disproportionately to total revenue, indicating strong market potential and expansion opportunities.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nExpand marketing efforts in high-potential cities.Geographic analysis revealed revenue concentration in key markets, highlighting opportunities for expansion.Increase marketing and operational focus in cities with strong revenue performance\n\n#### **7. Customer intent loss represents conversion inefficiency**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nA measurable percentage of bookings were cancelled, representing customer intent loss.Customers initially intended to purchase but did not complete the transaction.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nImprove booking experience and reliability.Intent loss rate analysis provided insight into customer drop-off, helping identify operational and experience improvement opportunities.\n\n#### **8. Some categories show weaker demand stability**\n\n***Business Insight***:\nBooking trends in certain categories fluctuate more significantly than others.Demand may be more price-sensitive or seasonal.\n\n***Business Recommendation***:\nImprove pricing and marketing strategies.The analysis showed that not all revenue growth is equally valuable. Some channels drove volume through heavy discounting, while others generated higher-quality revenue with lower churn risk. This highlights the importance of optimizing acquisition strategy for profitability, not just volume.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Business Impact Statement\nThis analysis enables stakeholders to identify revenue optimization opportunities, reduce revenue leakage, improve acquisition efficiency, and support data-driven strategic decision-making.\n\nThis dashboard provides a centralized performance monitoring solution that enables stakeholders to:\n\nTrack business performance in real time\n\nIdentify inefficiencies in the discount and channel strategy\n\nReduce revenue leakage due to cancellations\n\nImprove revenue optimization through data-driven insights\n\nSupport strategic decision-making\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **Conclusion**\n\nThis project demonstrates the use of Power BI to transform raw booking data into actionable business insights. \nThe dashboard enables performance monitoring, operational optimization, and strategic planning. It highlights core business analysis skills including KPI development, trend analysis, performance evaluation, and data-driven decision support.","metadata":{}}]}